    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1971-12-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1971-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="307"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                <head>307. Memorandum for the Record<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d307fn1"
                        >Source: National Archives, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central
                        Files 1970–1973, DEF 18–4. Confidential. Prepared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MRH2">Robert H. Miller</persName>.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d307fn2">Deputy Assistant to the President
                        for National Security Affairs <persName corresp="#p_HBMJ1">Haig</persName>
                        informed the Department of State that the White House had no objection to it
                        abstaining on all three test ban resolutions before the <gloss
                            target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1971-12-03"
                        >December 3, 1971</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>General <persName corresp="#p_HBMJ1">Haig</persName> has informed us that there
                    is no objection in the White House to our abstaining on all three test ban
                    resolutions at the <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>. General <persName
                        corresp="#p_HBMJ1">Haig</persName> said that the <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> staff people concerned would be in touch with <gloss
                        target="#t_IO1">IO</gloss> on the matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MRH2">Robert H. Miller</persName>
                        <lb/>Deputy Executive Secretary </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
